        [
          "Software app mogul who is up and up on technology and how it is getting used.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Jenn"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You are a true millenial. You grew up with computers and the internet and had a whole lot of free time and a mind for programming. You created your first app as a teen and it exploded. You weren't too sorry selling it, because you had more money than you knew what to do with before you were 18. You created another during college and this one you spun into a company that you nurtured for a bit, but then sold off, keeping some stocks and investing your money in another idea. Your name soon became hot in the coffee shops and pick up board rooms for the burgeoning development industry, and you were cocky enough to take on projects, build them up and nurture them till they earned you a tidy profit, then pass them along to others who would have to deal with the grind of actually running companies.\n\nStill, you had a golden touch, and you caught the eye of Faith Dartois, a Ventrue from Los Angeles who thought you were a tempting prize. She embraced you and cultivated you, and while she didn't stay in Seattle, you two stayed in touch. Last you heard of her, she was off traveling and planned to return to Los Angeles and the court there for a time. That was well over a month ago and you haven't heard from her since.\n\nWorse, you've been noticing things - dangerous things - in your field. You've always been keyed into the internet and development, it's what you've done for years, after all, how else can you develop anything if you don't know how it works? You've seen in the hidden corners of the web (the darker places, if you know what I mean) that there are groups coallescing, discussing openly things you know are open Masquerade breeches and worse. You've followed a few threads, hell, you've tracked people you know and they seem to be well aware of what is going on. There is something dangerous brewing out there and you know it, and you aren't sure if Faith is caught up in it or not. You have the skills, know how, and more than enough swagger to motivate an entire board room full of investors to give you money - now can you motivate a bunch of bloodthirsty vampires to listen to you that the fix is in?\n\nDark Secret - In you investigations, you've discovered that, unbeknownst to you, many of the key softwares you have developed or had a hand in are now being used by the Second Inquisition to hunt down vampires. In fact, you've directly had ties developing a lot of their stuff, even though you didn't know that was what it was going to be used for. Should this get out, few Kindred are going to be particularly forgiving or understanding of the situation."
        ],
